    "text": "Erdős Problem #741: declared status 'solved'. Formalized: yes. Let $A\\subseteq \\mathbb{N}$ be such that $A+A$ has positive density. Can one always decompose $A=A_1\\sqcup A_2$ such that $A_1+A_1$ and $A_2+A_2$ both have positive density?\n\nIs there a basis $A$ of order $2$ such that if $A=A_1\\sqcup A_2$ then $A_1+A_1$ and $A_2+A_2$ cannot both have bounded gaps? Prize: no. Tags: additive combinatorics.",
